<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870728-0136 </DOCNO><HL> Hong Kong's Trade Gap Grows</HL><DD> 07/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> FRESTMONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON) </IN><DATELINE> HONG KONG  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hong Kong's trade deficit widened to 1.13 billion Hong Kong dollars ($145 million) in June from 691 million dollars a year earlier, the government said.    Domestic exports rose 30% from the year before, to 16.29 billion dollars, while re-exports -- shipments of goods assembled from parts made elsewhere -- increased 53%, to 14.70 billion dollars. Total exports stood at 30.99 billion dollars, up 40%. Imports increased nearly 41%, to 32.13 billion dollars.    In the first half, the deficit widened to 6.23 billion dollars from 4.93 billion dollars a year earlier. Domestic exports gained 31%, to 85.79 billion dollars, and re-exports grew 51%, to 80.13 billion dollars, bringing total exports to 165.93 billion dollars, up 40%. Imports rose nearly 40%, to 172.16 billion dollars. </TEXT></DOC>